bubblesort: unmodified bsort benchmark, hence can't meassure some things
bsort_dryrun: runs bsort twice, first time without moving anything
bsort_swapping: two cells are always swapped trice, to increase ALU operations
bsort_branch: 4 additional comparisons at each step of the bsort, at different positions
bsort_branch_simple: 4 additional comparisons at each step of the bsort, at the same position

benchmark: number of instructions for 1 run in sunflower
number of cycles for 1 run in sunflower
number of fetched instructions for 1 run in sunflower

column2: place a 20 bit constant into top 20 bits of the rd register
add a constant to PC and save to rd register
load an 8bit value from memory, sign extended
load a 16bit value from memory, sign extended
load an 8bit value from memory, zero extended
load a 16bit value from memory, zero extended
bitwise AND an 11bit constant with register
make a request to the supporting execution environment
